# Zerodha enctoken bot on Render

This package gives you a small Flask admin panel that lets you manually paste a Zerodha `enctoken`, then run a background loop only during NSE market hours.

## Files
- `app.py` - Flask app, admin login, dashboard, health endpoint, worker loop.
- `requirements.txt` - Python dependencies.
- `render.yaml` - Render Blueprint for one-click deploy.
- `.gitignore` - Keeps secrets out of git.

## Local run
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
export ADMIN_PASSWORD='change-me'
python app.py

## Deploy on Render
Use New > Blueprint if `render.yaml` is present in the repo root, otherwise create a Web Service manually.
